            <div id="overview">
            <h2>Overview</h2>
            <p><strong>ALT Server</strong> is a server-oriented Linux distribution developed by <a href="https://www.basealt.ru/en" target="_blank">Basealt LLC</a> based on <a href="https://en.altlinux.org/Eleventh_Platform" target="_blank">the Eleventh Platform</a>.</p>
           </div>
        
            <div id="editions">
            <h2>Editions and Components</h2>
            <p>The ALT Server 11.0 distribution includes two product editions.</p>
            <p>An edition is a predefined set of components supported within a specific product. Editions can be switched using the alteratorctl console utility for managing modules and <a href="https://www.altlinux.org/Alteratorctl/editions_module" target="_blank">the dedicated edition selection module (RU)</a>. Edition selection is also available in the graphical interface: ACC → System → About System.</p>
            <p>Components are integrated sets of packages that deliver specific product functionality. Components are managed using the alt-components application (the new Component Management module in ACC) and <a href="https://www.altlinux.org/Alt-components" target="_blank">the components module (RU)</a> within the alteratorctl utility.</p>
			<h3>Currently, the distribution offers two editions:</h3>
