                 <div id="version-11.0-notes">
                <h3>Release Notes</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Previous version: <a href="https://www.altlinux.org/Альт_Сервер_10#10.4" title="ALT Server 10.4">ALT Server 10.4 (RU)</a>.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

                 <div id="version-11.0-changes">
                <h3>Changes compared to ALT Server 10</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Based on <a href="https://www.altlinux.org/Branches/p11" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Platform 11 stable repository branch (RU)</a>.</li>
                    <li>Rescue mode requires login as root with an empty password.</li>
                    <li>The system is installed in minimal mode — with or without a graphical interface. ALT Server and ALT Domain editions are available for installation.</li>
                    <li>New version of Alterator – <a href="https://www.altlinux.org/Alterator_on_D-Bus" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Alterator on D-Bus (RU)</a>.</li>
                    <li>Client applications include: alterator-explorer, ADT and alteratorctl.</li>
                    <li>New ACC module <a href="https://www.altlinux.org/Alt-components" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Components Manager (RU)</a> (alt-components application).</li>
                    <li>The distribution now features GNOME as its desktop environment.</li>
                    <li>Applications list on the desktop panel: Nautilus, Chromium (x86_64 only) or Firefox (for AArch64), Console, ACC.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
				
